        <p>A corporate venture capital (CVC) firm is an investment arm of a large corporation (like BNP Paribas). Unlike traditional VC firms that solely seek financial returns, CVCs often invest in startups to gain strategic advantages, access new technologies, or build partnerships.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
